iao_definition: ['Derivatives of ammonium compounds, (NH4(+))Y(-), in which all four of the hydrogens bonded to nitrogen have been replaced with univalent (usually organyl) groups.']
label: ['quaternary ammonium salt']

iao_definition: ['A frozen dessert usually made from dairy products, such as milk and cream, and often combined with fruits or other ingredients and flavours. Most varieties contain sugar, although some are made with other sweeteners. In some cases, artificial flavourings  and colourings are used in addition to (or in replacement of) the natural ingredients. This mixture is stirred slowly while cooling to prevent large ice crystals from forming; the result is a smoothly textured ice cream.']
label: ['ice cream food product']

iao_definition: ["A quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the amount of the bearer's there is mixed with another substance."]
label: ['concentration of']

iao_definition: ['A surfactant (or a mixture containing one or more surfactants) having cleaning properties in dilute solutions.']
label: ['detergent']

iao_definition: ['An antimicrobial agent that is applied to non-living objects to destroy harmful microorganisms or to inhibit their activity.']
label: ['disinfectant']

iao_definition: ['A country in Central Europe. It is bordered to the north by the North Sea, Denmark, and the Baltic Sea; to the east by Poland and the Czech Republic; to the south by Austria and Switzerland; and to the west by France, Luxembourg, Belgium, and the Netherlands. Germany comprises 16 states (Lander, Bundeslander), which are further subdivided into 439 districts (Kreise/Landkreise) and cities (kreisfreie Stadte).']
label: ['Germany']

iao_definition: ['When two or more amino acids combine to form a peptide, the elements of water are removed, and what remains of each amino acid is called an amino-acid residue.']
label: ['amino-acid residue']

iao_definition: ["A state of matter between a solid and a gas, in which a substance has the capacity to flow and conforms to the shape of the container. Liquids range from water to honey, corresponding to a range in viscosity (or apparent viscosity) from 1 to 500 centipoise (viscosity is a measure of a liquid's resistance to flow). Products that are pourable but have a higher viscosity are *SEMILIQUID*."]
label: ['food (liquid)']

iao_definition: ['The region of the digestive tract extending from the mouth cavity through pharynx esophagus stomach and duodenum.']
label: ['upper digestive tract']
obo_external_ontology_notes: ['WP: small intestine, large intestine, anus. Anal canal not part of LGIT according to FMA, but anus is considered part of LGIT according to WP. Duodenum overlaps both U/L. In Galen, entire GI tract excludes esophagus']

iao_definition: ['A food product not including meat and animal tissue products (such as gelatin or animal-derived rennet).']
label: ['vegetarian food product']
